args: I'm going to hold a recital in the castle!
I am going to hold a recital right here\nin this castle!
But ain't ya done with singin' and all that?
I have given up on giving up.
It's hard to believe I'm looking at the same\nwoman who was so determined to quit\njust a little while ago.
Are you certain about this decision?
Yes—and I do apologize for causing you\nall so much consternation.
Coming here and distancing myself from\nsinging for a while has allowed me to\nrealize something...

The one who was the most fixated on
being a songstress was myself—and
I have been acting like someone I'm not
in order to remain one.
But that ends now. From this point forward,\nI begin my life anew!
But why do you want to perform here?\nWhy not go somewhere bigger?
Yes, wouldn't you prefer a large\nperformance hall or the like?
You could have your pick of the litter—\nsurely any venue would move mountains\nto host your comeback show, yes?
No, I want to sing here; this is the place\nthat allowed me to be myself again.
I don't wish to stop being a songstress,\nbut I also don't wish to stop being Lucretia.
So that's why I want a fresh start in the\nplace where I can most easily be myself.
Then we'll be happy to help.
We'll need to do a lot of work before we\ncan host a recital.
True. We'll need to prepare a stage,\nfor starters.
Yeah, and call loads of people! Can't have\nthe songstress of the century beltin' out\ntunes without an audience, yeah?
Let's all pitch in and make sure Lucretia's\ncomeback performance is a success!
I can't believe I'm going to hear the\nfamous Lucretia sing!
I can't believe it either—I thought\nshe'd vanished?
First she disappears, and now she's \nsinging somewhere else? What a diva!
Let us not be too harsh on her; she DID\ninvite us here to make amends, after all.\nThe least we can do is listen politely.
Well, slop gravy on me and call me a\nham—there ain't an empty seat anywhere!
And the visitors just keep coming.\nLucretia's name really draws a crowd.
Not at all. I'm just happy to sing again.
It's been so long since I last felt happy\nbefore a performance.
I have you to thank for this,\n{player_name}.
I shall repay my debt with the best singing\nthat I can deliver.
Heh. Then it is time for me to begin.
That lady's got some nerve to just waltz\nout like nothin' happened.
Let us just be glad she's all right.
Thank you all for coming here tonight.
I want to take this moment to apologize\nfor worrying everyone with my sudden\ndisappearance.
I have always strived to be the perfect\nsongstress—to be what I believed the\nworld wanted me to be.
I thought doing this was more important\nthan anything—even being true to myself.\nBut I see now that I was mistaken.
I came to realize I would never be able to\ntruly sing from the heart so long as I kept\ndenying who I was.
But I am done trying to be someone else.\nFrom this point forward, I shall sing the\nsongs that truly speak to my heart!
If you are still interested in hearing me,\nI invite you to stay and listen.
(Ah, but they all must be so disappointed\nin me...)
(Still, I cannot blame them. I am the one\nwho has been running from who I really\nam all this time.)
Grace us with us your finest song!
She seems completely relaxed as well.\nWhatever was troubling her has clearly\nbeen washed away.
Perhaps. I'm simply glad she was able to\nrediscover her passion for music.
I've never heard anything like it!\nWelcome back, Lucretia!
...You there! I want her next recital booked\nbefore the night is out! Hurry now!
I'm glad that Lucretia was able to restore\nher reputation.
Was there ever any doubt?\nShe's the best at what she does.
Thank you all so much for your support.
I shall become a songstress once more!
